# Summary

1. Subject(s): Python, Graphic Design  
2. Topic or Unit of Study: Python w/ Turtle  
3. Grade/Level: 10th grade  
4. Objective: Students will use what they’ve learned so far in Turtle graphics to create an illustration with a theme of their choosing.  
5. Time Allotment: 1-3hrs

## Task 1: Project Requirements

You are going to be creating a picture in Turtle. Your illustration must meet a few requirements, but it can look however you want it to.

Requirements:

1. Must have a theme (ex. Galaxy theme)  
2. Must have at least **3** **different** 2-D shapes  
3. Must have a background color  
4. Must use at least **2** loops (ex. for loops)  
5. Must use at least **1** function 

LINK TO TURTLE DOCUMENTATION: [https://docs.python.org/3.7/library/turtle.html\#](https://docs.python.org/3.7/library/turtle.html#)

# Task 2: Learning the Syntax

**Movement**

`turtle.forward(78)` \- moves the pen forward by the specified distance

`turtle.backward(78)` \- moves the pen backward by the specified distance

`turtle.right(90)` \- turns the pen to the right by the specified angle

`turtle.left(90)` \- turns the pen to the left by the specified angle

**Design**

`turtle.pencolor(“red”)` \- sets pencolor to the color string 

`turtle.fillcolor(“yellow”)` \- sets fillcolor to the color string 

`turtle.color(“green”)` \- sets pencolor and fillcolor to the color string

Functions in Python:

A function is a user-defined block of code that only runs when it is called. You can pass data, such as a string, into a function. It will return data when it is called.

**Writing a function:**

```py
def myFunction(variable): # does not have to call a parameter
	# block of code/statements
```

**Calling a function:**

```py
myFunction(variable)  # does not have to call a parameter
```

***IF YOU DO NOT KNOW THE SYNTAX FOR SOMETHING, LOOK IT UP\!\!\!\!***
